canadian property catastrophe excess-of-loss reinsurance treaty.this contract, effective for the period july1, 2016 through and
including
june30, 2017, covers the accumulation of net property losses arising out of one occurrence on business written by the company's canadian businesses. the treaty covers all property written by
the company's canadian businesses for canadian insureds, including, but not limited to, habitational property, commercial property, inland marine, ocean marine and auto physical damages exposures,
with respect to risks located worldwide, written for canadian insureds. the treaty provides coverage for 50% of losses in excess of c$100million (us$74million at december31,
