shareholder return performance graph
the following graph shows a five-year comparison of the cumulative total return to shareholders for the company's common stock and the common
stock of companies included in the s&p500 index and the s&p500 property& casualty insurance index, which the company believes is the most appropriate comparative index.
(1)the
cumulative return to shareholders is a concept used to compare the performance of a company's stock over time and is the ratio of the net stock price change plus
the cumulative amount of dividends over the specified time period (assuming dividend reinvestment), to the stock price at the beginning of the time period.
(2)assumes
$100 invested in common shares of the travelers companies,inc. on december31, 2011.
