respectively.
the declaration and payment of future dividends to holders of the company's common stock will be at the discretion of the company's board of directors and will depend upon many factors, including the
company's financial position, earnings, capital requirements of the company's operating subsidiaries, legal requirements, regulatory constraints and other factors as the board of directors deems
relevant. dividends will be paid by the company only if declared by its board of directors out of funds legally available, subject to any other restrictions that may be applicable to the company. on
january24, 2017, the company announced that its board of directors
table of contents
declared
a regular quarterly dividend of $0.67 per share, payable march31, 2017, to shareholders of record on march10, 2017.
