real estate investments
on
at least an annual basis, the company obtains independent appraisals for substantially all of its real estate investments. in addition, the carrying value of all
real estate investments is reviewed for impairment on a quarterly basis or when events or changes in circumstances indicate that the carrying amount may not be recoverable. the review for impairment
considers the valuation from the independent appraisal, when applicable, and incorporates an estimate of the undiscounted cash flows
