if
the company determines that any of its deferred tax assets will not result in future tax benefits, a valuation allowance must be established for the portion of these assets that are
not expected to be realized. the valuation allowance increased by $3million in 2016 relating to the company's consolidated brazilian subsidiary. based upon a review of the company's
anticipated future taxable income, and also including all other available evidence, both positive and negative, the company's management concluded that it is more likely than not that the net deferred
tax assets will be realized.
for
